theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ interior A \ closure (B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `x` lies in the interior of `A \ B`.
  have hx_int_diff : x ∈ interior (A \ B : Set X) := hx
  -- Hence `x` lies in the interior of `A`, since `A \ B ⊆ A`.
  have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A := by
    have h_subset : (interior (A \ B : Set X) : Set X) ⊆ interior A :=
      interior_mono (Set.diff_subset _ _)
    exact h_subset hx_int_diff
  -- We now show `x ∉ closure B`.
  have hx_not_closureB : x ∉ closure (B : Set X) := by
    -- Suppose, towards a contradiction, that `x ∈ closure B`.
    intro hx_cl
    -- Use the neighbourhood characterization of `closure`.
    have h_nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff.1 hx_cl)
        (interior (A \ B : Set X)) isOpen_interior hx_int_diff
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hyB, hyInt⟩
    -- But `interior (A \ B)` is contained in `A \ B`, so `y ∉ B`.
    have hy_notB : y ∉ (B : Set X) := by
      have hy_in_diff : y ∈ (A \ B : Set X) := interior_subset hyInt
      exact hy_in_diff.2
    exact hy_notB hyB
  exact And.intro hx_intA hx_not_closureB

theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
  simpa using
    interior_mono (Set.diff_subset : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A)
